    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-beef-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pork & beef mince </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-beef-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is browning, peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>roughly</p><p>Once starting to brown, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and <strong>diced tomato </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-beef-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tagliatelle for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the tagliatelle, reserving 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span>of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-beef-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, add your <strong>dried basil </strong>and <strong>dried oregano </strong>to the pan with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-beef-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> beef stock mix</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>and 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[110ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span>of the <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>bolognese rag\u00f9</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-beef-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained tagliatelle </strong>to the bolognese rag\u00f9<strong> </strong>and give everything a gentle mix up</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-beef-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bolognese rag\u00f9</strong> <strong>with fresh tagliatelle </strong>topped with your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
